SIMPLE: heady
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heady
<hw>Head"y</hw> <pr>(h⟦ecr⟧d"⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Head</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Willful; rash; precipitate;
hurried on by will or passion; ungovernable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the talent required is to be hot, to be <qex>heady</qex>, --
to be violent on one side or the other.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Temple.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Apt to affect the head; intoxicating;
strong.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The liquor is too <qex>heady</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Violent; impetuous.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>heady</xex>
currance.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heal</ent>⟦br⟧
